          h2.bs-docs-heading Mobile Grids
          p
            | There are 2 different options for grids below the 768 breakpoint: 
            strong Mobile-Grid
            |  and 
            strong No-Grid
            | . The small-screen grid will override the 
            code
              | .grid
            | , 
            code
              | .slimgrid
            |  or 
            code
              | .slimgrid5
            | &nbsp;classes, and should be used in addition to them.

          h4.bs-docs-heading(style='padding-top:20px;') Mobile-Grid
          p
            | The mobile-grid utilizes 
            strong 6 fluid columns
            | . To implement, add the appropriate m&#8209;grid class 
            strong in addition 
            | to your primary 
            code
              | .grid
            |  class. Class options are 
            code
              | .m&#8209;grid&#8209;at&#8209;979
            | , 
            code
              | .m&#8209;grid&#8209;at&#8209;767
            | , 
            code
              | .m&#8209;grid&#8209;at&#8209;567
            | , 
            code
              | .m&#8209;grid&#8209;at&#8209;479
            |  or 
            code
              | .m&#8209;grid
            |  (same as 
            code
              | .m&#8209;grid&#8209;at&#8209;767
            |  );
            |  and add the appropriate 
            code
              | .m-span
            |  and (optionally) 
            code
              | .m-offset
            |  class to each column - again, in addition to the primary 
            code
              | .span
            |  class. The total mobile spans/offsets need to add up to 6.
          p.p4
            | Resize your browser to below 768px wide to see the mobile grid take effect.
            br
            | Hover over any of the columns to see the actual class names that affect it.

